House Resolution 907
By: Representatives Henderson of the 113th, Lupton of the 83rd, and Gilliard of the 162nd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Archie S. Shepherd; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, a native of Covington, Georgia, Archie S. Shepherd devoted decades of his life
3 to advocacy, civil rights, and community service, greatly impacting the citizens of Newton
4 County through his enduring commitment to social justice; and
5 WHEREAS, his leadership within the Newton County NAACP included serving as President
6 from 1998 to 2006 and Chairperson of the Legal Redress Committee from 2006 to 2014,
7 earning him honors such as the 2004 Humanitarian Award and a proclamation declaring
8 November 17, 2006, as "Archie Shepherd Day" in recognition of his dedication; and
9 WHEREAS, he significantly impacted the youth of Newton County through his founding of
10 the Sam McLurkin Council #75, Order of the Knights of Pythagoras, in 2008, providing
11 mentorship and leadership development opportunities; and
12 WHEREAS, he further expanded his community advocacy in March 2015 by organizing and
13 serving as President of the Newton County Chapter of the National Action Network (NAN),
14 for which he received the Dorothy Irene Height Trailblazer Award for Social Justice in
15 November 2015; and
