16 WHEREAS, his exemplary involvement with Prince Hall Masonic Friendship Lodge #20
17 spanned over 50 years of distinguished service as member and Past Worshipful Master, for
18 which he received awards such as the Outstanding Service Award, Longevity Award, and
19 the Purple Jacket marking his 50-year milestone; and
20 WHEREAS, his contributions to the community also included ten years of dedicated service
21 on the Medical Board of the Willing Helpers Medical Clinic, service on the City of
22 Covington Housing Board of Adjustments and Appeals, active participation on the Northeast
23 Georgia Aging Services Advisory Council Board, and advocacy for workers as Chief Union
24 Steward of Local #42 AFL-CIO-CLC; and
25 WHEREAS, he was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
26 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example he made of his life, he
27 made this world a better place in which to live; and
28 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Archie S. Shepherd will long be
29 remembered for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
30 had the great fortune of knowing him.
31 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
32 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Archie S. Shepherd and
33 express their deepest and most sincere regret at his passing.
34 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
35 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
36 family of Archie S. Shepherd.
